<br>
I hotbar positionals like Glacial Movement (side style) or a nice Havoc (front style).  Between the 2 I would go with GM (side) b/c GM has better &quot;to hit&quot; bonus as well as a defense bonus (Havoc has a defense penalty).  I would only use Havoc IF I had the lvl 50 style Tyr's b/c it does BIG damage and chains off of Havoc.  Of course Tyr's has the bleed effect so your target cant be mezzed but if you're hitting him mezz wont stick anyway.  You could also go with Evernight (rear position); it does nice damage for small end use and chains to arctic rift another high damage style with low end use.  You also have cleave/thryms chain  (parry dependent) which is low end use and high damage but you pbly wont parry enough for this to be useful.  Lastly you have Plague which is an anytime style that taunts and uses medium endurance and has a medium penalty to defense.  I would personally rank it in this order:<br>
<br>
IF you have 50 &quot;natural&quot; axe (read as have Tyr's):<br>
<br>
1)Havoc(front) with Plague backup.  This way you are gonna hit with a style no matter what.  Even if Havoc doesn't fire b/c you are not properly positioned, Plague will.  Then IF Havoc fires you go with Tyr's with Plague back up next round.<br>
<br>
2)Evernight(rear) with Plague backup.  This way you are gonna hit with a style no matter what.  Even if Evernight doesn't fire b/c you are not properly positioned, Plague will.  Then IF Evernight fires you go with Arctic Rift with Plague back up next round.  IF you are chasing a runner this option is actually #1 option.<br>
<br>
3)Glacial Movement with Plague backup.<br>
<br>
4)Cleave/Thrym's.  Dont bother for the most part unless you have REAL HIGH parry.<br>
<br>
In large scale battles (RvR as opposed to PvP or GvG) I find that the same stuff works.  However, in large scale battles your tactic will most definitely be different.  The styles will work but you dont want to be going head to head with too many other characters.  You'd be better off avoiding tanks, light tanks and going for musicians and robed casters/healers.<br>
<br>
   <p>Albron<br>
Level 50 Norse Skald<br>
